title: The Secret Garden
creator: Frances Hodgson Burnett
description: Librivox recording of The Secret Garden, by Frances Hodgson Burnett. Read by Kara Shallenberg Mary Lennox is a spoiled, middle-class, self-centred child who has been recently orphaned. She is accepted into the quiet and remote country house of an uncle, who has almost completely withdrawn into himself after the death of his wife. Mary gradually becomes drawn into the hidden side of the house: why does she hear the crying of a unseen child? Why is there an overgrown, walled garden, its door long locked? (Summary by Peter) Read by Kara Shallenberg For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audiobooks, or to become a volunteer reader, please visit librivox.org. Download M4B (197mb)
subject: literature; audiobook; children; librivox
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
One of my very favorite Librivox books.

Sep. 2014:  I just listened to it again.  This is a very very strong candidate for the best book ever read on Librivox, or anyplace else for that matter.  No one, including any professional reader, could have possibly read this book better than Kara "Kayray" Shallenberg. Twenty-five stars!
I have enjoyed this high quality recording. Hence I have linked it on the Wikipedia page for the book.

This is a classic so no summary really necessary.  The reader does a very good job with character voices.  I also noticed birds chirping in the background, which I thought added a nice bit of sound effects to the reading.  Thank you!
